result.execSummary:
The defendant Jedediah E Christianson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Cause Child 13-18 to View Sex. Activity [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.055(1).
  • Exposing Genitals/Pubic Area/Intimate Parts to a Child [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.10(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Case called at 3:09 pm [Clerk SH]
Defendant Jedediah E Christianson in court with Attorney Yelena Olegovna Zarwell. DA Susan Happ appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Constitutional rights reviewed; maximum penalties recited; plea of "Guilty" entered on Counts #1 & #2; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds the Defendant  guilty, and orders JOC entered.

On Count #1, the Court sentences Mr. Christianson to 4 years, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of 2 years and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 2 years, consecutive to any other previously imposed sentence. This sentence is IMPOSED & STAYED and the Court places the Defendant on Probation for 4 years, concurrent, with conditions:

On Count #2, the Court sentences Mr. Christianson to 3 years, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of 2 years and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 1 year, consecutive to Count #1. This sentence is IMPOSED & STAYED and the Court places the Defendant on Probation for 4 years, concurrent, with conditions:

Conditions of Probation for Count #1 & #2:
--To serve 12 months in the Jefferson County Jail, with Huber/Work-Release privileges (Ct#1 only) to commence 12/17/14 at 6:00 pm 
--Defendant is required to report for commencement and service of the jail term with absolute sobriety and without non-prescribed controlled substances in system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber/Work-Release privileges without further process.
--No contact with any female under the age of 18 years, without Agent approval
--No possession/use of any electronic device capable of accessing the internet, without prior approval from Agent
--psychosexual or psychological evaluation & follow-through with any treatment, per Agent
--To undergo any other assessment, treatment or counseling as per Agent
--To obtain/maintain employment and/or education program or combination of the two, per Agent
--To pay costs of $536 ($268 each count)
--To pay $500 DNA Surcharge ($250 each count)
--To submit DNA Sample upon demand (Ct#1)
--To pay $68 summons fees (Ct#1)
--Sex offender registration pursuant to 301.45(5)

Felony Firearm and Voting-rights prohibitions/warnings given
Explanation of Determinate Sentence form given to the Defendant

If revoked, The Court finds that the Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program (Boot Camp) and the Substance Abuse Program. 
If revoked, The Court gives 0 days credit for time already served.
Court informs Mr. Christianson that if probation is closed when he arrives there today, then he shall report to probation 12/18/14 by 4:00 pm
